   {:e #blake3 "c9efd86158b536bc703d7ef81ce5f8e1d94f6ab7005c0677e2d3333ada56bd3a" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: An agent with 226 observations cannot navigate them. No braid observe list/search/show exists. The agent fell back to reading markdown — the exact failure C9 solves. PRINCIPLE: Every braid output is a STEERING EVENT on the LLM's latent space manifold (ADR-FOUNDATION-030). The observe subcommands must navigate the knowledge manifold, not just list data. A flat list of 226 observations sorted by timestamp is the worst possible steering. KERNEL SIDE — all_observations(store) -> Vec<ObservationSummary>: New function in concept.rs. ObservationSummary struct: entity (EntityId), title (String, first 80 chars), body (String, full), confidence (f64), category (Option<String>), concept_name (Option<String> from :exploration/concept ref), concept_entity (Option<EntityId>), timestamp (u64 from datom.tx.wall_time()), tags (Vec<String>), agent_name (String from datom.tx.agent hex), link_count (usize, count of :exploration/depends-on + :exploration/related-spec refs). Iterates store.attribute_datoms(:exploration/body), enriches via store.live_value and store.entity_datoms. Sorted by timestamp descending. CLI SIDE — Four subcommands added to braid observe: (1) braid observe list [--concept FILTER] [--limit N]: Groups observations by concept cluster. Each group shows: concept name, member count, confidence range, most-surprising member (highest surprise score). Top 5 clusters by default. Within each cluster, show top 3 observations by confidence. Format: [concept-name] (N obs, conf 0.85-0.95) followed by indented observation titles. Steers agent toward knowledge STRUCTURE. (2) braid observe search PATTERN [--sort relevance|confidence|recent] [--limit N]: Substring match on body text, then RANK by composite score: 0.4*keyword_relevance + 0.3*link_count_normalized + 0.2*confidence + 0.1*recency. Default sort: relevance. Shows: confidence, truncated body, concept membership. Steers agent toward most IMPORTANT matches. (3) braid observe show ENTITY: Full detail view. Body, confidence, category, concept membership, tags, timestamp, agent. PLUS: incoming links (observations that depend on this one, via VAET on :exploration/depends-on), outgoing links (what this depends on, via :exploration/depends-on datoms). Shows the observation in its GRAPH CONTEXT. Steers agent to understand structural position. (4) braid observe recent [N]: Most recent N observations (default 20) with concept assignment. Format: timestamp, confidence, concept tag, truncated title. Steers agent to see recent THEMES. CLAP STRUCTURE: braid observe is currently positional TEXT for creation. Convert to subcommand-based with backward compat: 'braid observe TEXT' remains valid for creation (either as default subcommand or via clap positional fallback). 'braid observe list', 'braid observe search', 'braid observe show', 'braid observe recent' are new subcommands. REUSES: all_observations() mirrors all_tasks() pattern. Concept grouping reuses concept_inventory(). Link count reuses store.entity_datoms(). Search ranking reuses connections::tokenize() + jaccard. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid observe list shows observations grouped by concept with member counts. (B) braid observe search AUDIT returns audit observations ranked by composite score. (C) braid observe show ENTITY shows full detail with incoming/outgoing links. (D) braid observe recent 10 shows 10 most recent with concept tags. (E) braid observe TEXT -c 0.9 still creates observations (backward compat). (F) All 4 output modes work (human, agent, json, tsv). (G) On the live store with 226 audit observations, braid observe search AUDIT returns them ranked with the highest-linked, highest-confidence observations first. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (all_observations), crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs (subcommands), crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs (clap definitions). EFFORT: 8h." :op :assert}
